00:41:42.450 --> 00:41:46.170
So basically the bottom
line is the human voice

00:41:46.170 --> 00:41:49.980
creates sound that
exists within physics.

00:41:49.980 --> 00:41:51.570
And we are able
to sing in better

00:41:51.570 --> 00:41:55.060
tune than a piano or a
guitar because they're really

00:41:55.060 --> 00:41:57.780
locked to this well-tempered
tuning system that

00:41:57.780 --> 00:41:59.287
is fundamentally imperfect.

00:41:59.287 --> 00:42:00.870
We made this trade
off so that then we

00:42:00.870 --> 00:42:02.480
could have harmonic changes.

00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:04.940
Otherwise, what you get is
like Indian classical music,

00:42:04.940 --> 00:42:08.080
which remains in the same key,
the same mode, the same raga

00:42:08.080 --> 00:42:08.904
the whole time.

00:42:08.904 --> 00:42:10.570
And you can have a
melody, but you don't

00:42:10.570 --> 00:42:12.316
have any harmonic changes.

00:42:12.316 --> 00:42:13.440
Those are your two options.

00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:17.600
So I think it's a good trade,
but it's still imperfect

00:42:17.600 --> 00:42:20.020
The one thing I really do
think about when I'm arranging

00:42:20.020 --> 00:42:22.570
is keeping the voices
spread very much

00:42:22.570 --> 00:42:25.630
the way that exists in the
physics of sound, the harmonic

00:42:25.630 --> 00:42:26.350
series.

00:42:26.350 --> 00:42:28.055
You can look it up
online, Wikipedia.

00:42:28.055 --> 00:42:32.380
I'm sure Google has their own
several pages somewhere online

00:42:32.380 --> 00:42:34.350
of the harmonic
series and the way

00:42:34.350 --> 00:42:37.620
that every note casts a
number of harmonics above it.

00:42:37.620 --> 00:42:39.120
To make a long story
short, it means

00:42:39.120 --> 00:42:42.640
keeping your bass notes low and
your other voices closer voiced

00:42:42.640 --> 00:42:43.480
up above.

00:42:43.480 --> 00:42:46.004
Because what that does is it
allows you to tune more easily.

00:42:46.004 --> 00:42:47.670
And what I try to do
in my arrangements,

00:42:47.670 --> 00:42:51.330
as much as there's a lot of joy
in them and a lot of complexity

00:42:51.330 --> 00:42:54.250
is to make it easy for people
to do things like tune,

00:42:54.250 --> 00:42:56.490
so then they can focus on
connecting with an audience

00:42:56.490 --> 00:42:58.865
and emoting rather than spending
their entire time having

00:42:58.865 --> 00:43:01.060
to worry about the mechanics
of what's going on.

00:43:01.060 --> 00:43:03.950
So that's really my go to.

00:43:03.950 --> 00:43:04.450
Yeah.

