00:44:47.530 --> 00:44:49.400
DEKE SHARON: Well, one of the
great things about a capella

00:44:49.400 --> 00:44:51.430
is once people fall in love with
the sound of the human voice,

00:44:51.430 --> 00:44:54.330
they're much more likely to move
into different styles of music.

00:44:54.330 --> 00:44:57.840
In fact, singers are able
to blend styles more easily

00:44:57.840 --> 00:44:59.180
than other styles of music.

00:44:59.180 --> 00:45:01.320
So you go to a King's
Singer's concert

00:45:01.320 --> 00:45:03.310
and they start out
singing early music.

00:45:03.310 --> 00:45:05.240
And then they go into
20th century classical.

00:45:05.240 --> 00:45:07.210
And they may sing some
classical choral music.

00:45:07.210 --> 00:45:09.940
And then they go and they
sing some early folk Americana

00:45:09.940 --> 00:45:13.276
and maybe some jazz
and end with some pop.

00:45:13.276 --> 00:45:14.650
No instrumentalist
could do that.

00:45:14.650 --> 00:45:16.380
Because they'd need like
early music instruments

00:45:16.380 --> 00:45:17.600
like recorders and sackbuts.

00:45:17.600 --> 00:45:19.600
And then they'd need an
entire string orchestra.

00:45:19.600 --> 00:45:22.070
And then they'd need some
world music instruments

00:45:22.070 --> 00:45:23.930
and a jazz combo
and a rock band.

00:45:23.930 --> 00:45:25.522
Like it's never done.

00:45:25.522 --> 00:45:27.230
So you're able to
travel around the world

00:45:27.230 --> 00:45:28.938
more effectively with
your voice than you

00:45:28.938 --> 00:45:31.560
are with any other
style of music--

00:45:31.560 --> 00:45:33.804
or any other instrumentation,
more correctly.

00:45:33.804 --> 00:45:36.220
And the beautiful thing about
what's going on in a capella

00:45:36.220 --> 00:45:38.761
now-- and you may not see this
with Pentatonix or on YouTube.

00:45:38.761 --> 00:45:42.360
But the fact of the matter is
different styles of a capella

00:45:42.360 --> 00:45:45.170
are becoming more popular
based on their local roots.

00:45:45.170 --> 00:45:48.750
So you go to Taiwan which
has a tremendous tradition

00:45:48.750 --> 00:45:50.100
of a capella singing.

00:45:50.100 --> 00:45:52.330
And you get a group
like O-Kai Singers who

00:45:52.330 --> 00:45:56.050
are blending Taiwanese pop music
with this traditional Taiwanese

00:45:56.050 --> 00:45:56.550
style.

00:45:56.550 --> 00:45:58.720
Or when I made the
"Sing-Off" in China,

00:45:58.720 --> 00:46:01.350
we were taking Chinese songs
and blending them with popular

00:46:01.350 --> 00:46:01.850
idioms.

00:46:01.850 --> 00:46:05.500
So you'd get some old
Maoist song with disco beat.

00:46:05.500 --> 00:46:07.390
We just had a lot of
fun being really crazy

00:46:07.390 --> 00:46:11.190
and creating a new sound and
style of contemporary Chinese

00:46:11.190 --> 00:46:12.220
a capella.

00:46:12.220 --> 00:46:14.510
And for anybody who's
in America thinking

00:46:14.510 --> 00:46:16.590
like, well, but everything's
homogenized here.

00:46:16.590 --> 00:46:18.490
There's no real sense of place.

00:46:18.490 --> 00:46:23.280
I tell you, so little has been
done and so much still exists.

00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:26.400
First of all, where's the
great Hawaiian a capella group?

00:46:26.400 --> 00:46:29.080
Where's the great Cajun
a capella group, right?

00:46:29.080 --> 00:46:31.980
We just, on the "Sing-Off,"
created the first ever country

00:46:31.980 --> 00:46:34.010
a capella group with Home Free.

00:46:34.010 --> 00:46:35.970
There's a vast--
where's the great Latin

00:46:35.970 --> 00:46:38.350
a capella that's
going to tear up-- I

00:46:38.350 --> 00:46:39.600
was hoping Nota would do that.

00:46:39.600 --> 00:46:42.070
And Vocal Sampling
from Cuba's tremendous.

00:46:42.070 --> 00:46:44.550
But there's still so
much, so many stones

00:46:44.550 --> 00:46:46.100
we that haven't been uncovered.

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:48.560
Plus you can blend
these different styles.

00:46:48.560 --> 00:46:53.160
Take Six took gospel
melodies, jazz harmonies,

00:46:53.160 --> 00:46:56.440
R&amp;B stylings and created a
style that's all their own.

00:46:56.440 --> 00:47:00.220
And now they've got dozens
of Grammys as a result of it.

00:47:00.220 --> 00:47:03.070
Within a capella, there
are so many frontiers that

00:47:03.070 --> 00:47:05.140
haven't even been bridged yet.

00:47:05.140 --> 00:47:07.370
